                <p><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"><b><span class="spnMessageText"><a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=6528" title="View Cuku's Profile" onMouseOver="(window.status='View Cuku\'s Profile'); return true" onMouseOut="(window.status=''); return true">Cuku</a></span></b></font><br />
                <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"><small>Pile of Bones</small></font><br />
                <td bgcolor="#333366" width="100%" colspan="2" valign="top">
                  <table width="100%" height="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
                    <tr>
                      <td valign="top">
                      <img src="images/icon_mi_1.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="" title="" hspace="3" /><font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2">Posted&nbsp;-&nbsp;10/05/2002&nbsp;:&nbsp; 12:50:33 AM</font>
                      &nbsp;<a href="pop_profile.asp?mode=display&id=6528"><img src="images/icon_profile.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="Show Profile" title="Show Profile" align="absmiddle" hspace="6" /></a>
                      &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=TopicQuote&TOPIC_ID=9326&FORUM_ID=6"><img src="images/icon_reply_topic.gif" width="15" height="15" border="0" alt="Reply with Quote" title="Reply with Quote" align="absmiddle" hspace="6" /></a>
                      <hr noshade size="2"></td>
                    </tr>
                    <tr>
           	<td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white">
                      <font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> <br />>>This is a LONG letter I sent, and will continue to send to VI until I get an answer or feedback about wtf they see as our role in EQ now. As you can see I have tendacy to ramble, but I had to at least try. Please don't flame the nit-picking minor issues you may find, but feel free to add concepts that you guys/gals may think will help define us.<br /><br /><br /><br />Hello Guys,<br /><br />First, I wanted to say I think VI has done a great job on EQ. I have enjoyed playing this game since it went commercial three years ago.<br /><br />Please take the time to read this letter completely, I took a lot of time and effort to put this into a spreadsheet and concepts. I know you guys are very busy with PoP stuff, but I thought these issues needed to be addressed while you are still in the testing phase for spells.<br /><br />If this was sent to the wrong people, please forward this on to who ever has the authority to make changes or to answer some of my concerns.<br /><br />I play a level 60 Iksar Necromancer on FV server. I like this class the best of all I have played so far. I play in a top guild here, and have about 60 AA so far. So, I’ve seen  all the low-mid-high end areas so far, and there are only a couple uber mobs we haven’t tried yet.<br /><br />I have some GRAVE (no pun intended ) concerns about the direction of the Necro Class.  I wanted to state some concerns, offer some suggestions, and get your feed-back on some issues, before I consider to stop playing EQ.<br /><br />I am curious about what VI sees  as the Necromancer’s role on raids. In other words, what defining role are we supposed to do? Chanters debuff, mezz, haste, rune etc, Magi summon, DS, make rods, Coth, use DD spells and monster pets, Wiz nuke for ungodly amounts now, melee = DPS and tankage, Clerics heal, buff, rez, Druids heal great now, buff, DD, Shaman slow, buff, Dot, debuff, and also are great healers now.<br /><br />Necromancers used to be needed for mana transferring on raids. But, now with new Magi rods, we aren’t needed for mana. We were also called on at some points to do group healing, and some spam healing at times. But, with new heal spells for druids, shaman, and new ones for ranger/pally coming, there is no need for our weak heals. Sometimes we are asked for group taps, but with all the new buffs coming in PoP, our small group tap buffs will be called on less because there is only so many buffs a person can have up at a time, and ours won’t impact as much as others will. So, with mana transferring no longer being a needed necro skill, as well as our heals and group taps not having much impact anymore. I wonder what our role is.<br /><br />I’m thinking it’s dealing damage through our dots. At least that’s what I expect you to say as your answer :)<br /><br />So, I did a spreadsheet (attached) on our spells so I could see the facts about  what damage we do. The first table is a typical spell cycle I use when soloing. I want to add a couple caveats to the spreadsheet. First, most Necromancer’s do not have Funeral Pyre like I do. Most mobs are resistant to at least one line of our dots, so rarely if ever do I get a chance to land all the dots shown.  Also, very few mobs will allow me to dark them, and those that can be darked have really high resists on dark line. (bad mobs bad) J So, most Necro’s I know all use dooming darkness because its less mana, fast cast, and  lasts as long as most other darks. But I wanted to see best case scenario so I listed the top dark spells in spell cycle. <br /><br />Let me define a couple abbreviations I used.  DPT = Damage per Tick. DPM = Damage per Mana used. DPS = Damage per Second. DPS/24 sec = I used this to see how much damage DD casters could do in a 24 sec cycle. I figured up how much damage a caster could do in a 24 sec timeframe, including casting time, recast time, and divided the damage by 24 secs. I felt this was a more realistic view of DD damage because some classes have recast time on spells, and if I didn’t include the recast time in formula it would look like they were doing more damage than they really were.<br /><br />I also did not use any class’s ancient spells in spreadsheet. They are to rare to be useful to all but a few of us, and all were very similar in damage anyway.<br /><br />I looked at damage per second, damage per tick, and damage per mana used.  What I found was, necromancers under  certain circumstances  can do some very decent damage if the mob isn’t resistant to fire or magic spells or immune to changes in run speeds.  Realistically though, on raids in ToV, Sssraa Temple, etc you really can only get funeral, pyro, splurt (as long as no chanters are using asphyxiate because it doesn’t stack with that spell even though mine is much more powerful) and vexing in a normal cycle.  If mobs are not the uber mobs in zone that will take at least 10+ min to fight, then no sense even dotting because mobs are dead well before dot can take full effect. So, I normally try to cast  my life tap spell and do some damage where I can. I did not factor in our Pet either because…. basically they suck on raids.  The AE spells from the top mobs kill pets to quickly so no one really uses pets on most  mobs. In the cases where we can use pets, its embarrassing how bad our lvl 59 pets deal out damage. The damage per hit is nice at 73 for a focused pet, but the problem is the pet’s attack score is so weak it can barely even hit lvl 55+ mobs. Hopefully the new pets in PoP will be better.<br /><br />When I looked at the best case scenario damage from my dots it didn’t look to bad. It’s only when I look at reality scenarios I get a bit depressed. <br /><br />I value my class, and my guild. I want to be able to contribute to the success of my guild’s raids. But, I and most other people in EQ are starting to realize necro’s are really not a needed class anymore. While I can at times add  about 100 dps, most of the time it’s about 70-80 dps. That concerns me because that’s an average to below average contribution for a dps class.  We used to be needed for other things in addition to DPS, but now that no one needs us for anything besides damage, I’m not really able to contribute as much as I used too. <br /><br />I was hoping that new spells in PoP would address the changes to our class. However, when I looked at the posted new necro spells I began to consider leaving EQ after three years. My only hope is that all the necro spells are not yet posted. <br /><br />The upgrade to our poison dots is a nice addition. The upgrade to vexing is also nice.  The upgrade to dark line was simply a 2 tick extension  of our current dark spell. No increase in damage per tick or DPS. It is a bit more mana efficient though.  However, its not a spell most Necro will use to dark mobs. It is 425 mana, 6 sec cast time and only last 15 ticks. Dooming darkness is 120 mana, 4 sec cast time, and last 15 ticks. So given the amount of  times the dark line is resisted, it’s a better to use dooming when u need to snare. Darkness isn’t  used by most of us to damage mobs, its used for snaring.  The Dark Plague spell I thought  was  joke VI was playing on Necro class to see how bent out of shape we would get. :) I sure hope it is a joke, because a lvl 65 spell that does 90 damage per tick is not one I or anyone my level will use.  <br /><br />(Note: I have no problem at all with any of the new PoP spells when I’m soloing, my concern its how they effect my ability to contribute to raids and be a useful member of my guild. At my level, you either participate in guild raids etc or you quit EQ because there is nothing else left to do. I love EQ, my class, and my guild and I want to keep playing. So, I thought I would voice my concerns and see if it can prompt changes before I consider leaving.)<br /><br />I have to say that I wonder if there is a dedicated person assigned to the Necro Class on the VI development team. Because I do not think anyone is really paying attention to this class. I’m guessing who ever is assigned to our class has many other things to do and isn’t really aware of our needs.  Let give you a some examples of why I feel that way. <br /><br />1. If we used best case scenario for typical dot cycle and even included Embracing Darkness. The net effect of PoP dot improves for the Necro class is only 9.5 more damage per tick total . (see spreadsheet lines 12-20). It seems someone just looked at what spells we had and said ok lets add a little bit to this one and that one. <br />NONE of the new PoP dots exceed  Funeral Pyre in DPT or  Funeral & Pyro in Total Damage. None of them exceeded the efficiency of Splurt, Funeral, or Pyro. So, while the upgrades to the spells themselves are nice upgrades to that line, they do not help me do hardly any more damage on raids. Assuming again that we can land all the spells listed on spreadsheet, the increase in damage is 7%, while the increase in efficiency is only 1.94%. While that may seem like a nice little bump in damage to you, the reality is that the bulk of that increase comes from the poison dot and dark spell. The majority of high end raids are in Ssrra and ToV, both of which have mobs with a insanely high innate resistance to poison and disease and most immune to changes in run speed. So, poison/dark spells don’t really get used a lot on raids. <br /><br />2. Since changes to EQ over the last 6 months have reduced the need for many of our support spells. Our main asset to raids now is our ability to deal damage. However, PoP has ZERO new regular DD for necro, and ZERO new Undead DD for necro. As its stands now, every caster class can out nuke me, and ranger’s/sk’s can nuke for nearly as much as me on non MR resistant mobs. On MR resistant mobs, ranger/sk can actually out nuke me (See Spreadsheet lines 49-86). My point being, that it doesn’t appear anyone even looked at our damage output capability since lvl 44. And they certainly didn’t look for PoP spells.<br /><br />3. Another example of inattentiveness to our class….Ever since focus effect items have been introduced into the game. Necromancer DD spells ignite/chill bones, and insidious retrogression are not considered DD by focus items even though there is no dot effect on them. It’s been many patches since this has been an issue and it is still not fixed. It’s bad enough our DD’s suck and have a 12 second recast time on them, but we can’t even make them slightly better with focus items.<br /><br />4. Yet another example… Epic Weapon - This has been an issue for at least 18 months now. The drop rate on necro epic items is horrendous. I have been to fear and killed 38 named Golems/CT and no slime blood yet. The drop rate on other items isn’t much better. Run a que on epics in EQ over all servers, and see what caster class has the least amount. Heck, run it for all classes, I’d bet we have the fewest. With the possible exception of warrior/sk/pally, but that’s probably because there are tons of weapons out there now that are better than their epic.<br /><br />5. AA Skills - First, I wanted to say thanks for the addition of combat stability and agility, as well as natural durability. Those skills help me a lot because I tank instead of my weak pet, and they help me take less damage and they add hps which is always a good thing for necro’s.<br /><br />There are a couple things that make me think no one gave our AA’s much thought though and simply copied and pasted from other classes, and then hastened to add a couple useless skills cause they ran out of time. <br />First, General skills are fine, Arch are also good, except the Spell Casting Deftness doesn’t really apply to this class.  <br /><br />Class AA - :( <br />MGB skill - would be good if we actually had  group spells to use. However, the only group spell we have is a ultra rare drop off a rare mob deep in Chardok. No one on my server even has the spell, or frankly would want it. I have no idea why its placed in such an off the wall spot.<br /><br />FearStorm - I was all excited about this one. Seeing as how we are the masters of fear and all. Then, I find out that mobs over lvl 52 resist it like they do all other fear spells. So, it’s a useless raid skill, which makes it useless to our class.<br /><br />Deadmez - Useful in maybe 2 places in all of EQ. Again I thought maybe because we are masters of the undead, we could mezz higher lvl stuff, but someone forgot to tell the mobs 54+ they supposed to be mezzed when I cast this.<br /><br />Mend Companion - A heal I can use every 2hrs and 24 min. :) Might be useful if it's reuse time was 3 min. But if I need to heal a pet, and shadowbond can’t handle it then my pet will just have to die. I can CH my pet with Shadowbond every 2 min if needed, why would I want this useless skill? And with new pet heal coming in PoP, this AA is now as bad as the MGB skill.<br /><br />Flesh to Bone - cute<br /><br />Innate ITU - I can’t think of where I would use this, but it cant hurt to have.<br /><br />Pet Discipline, Dire Charm, Call to Corpse - Good job on these!<br /><br />Life burn - Still undecided on this one. The fact you can’t critical with it, can’t have focus items effect damage, and the fact it’s possible that it won’t stick on mob, and you get low hp aggro when you cast it are serious drawbacks. But it shows potential and I need to pick something to get class title.<br /><br /><br /><br />6. PoP AA - Granted the skills listed here, as well as all the other spells I spoke of earlier are not written in stone yet, but conceptually these will work for my argument. These top four  are prime examples of someone not spending time to develop something new and just regurgitates something that was already there. Or in the case of FD pet gave no thought at all.<br /><br />Pet FD - Why? How is that feature helpful to us at all? <br />Recall Pet - Unless there are new pet rules in PoP, how is this useful? We summon max pet every cast now.<br /><br />Hastened Call to Corpse- This is an example of how no one spent any time on our AA…. Again :( All guilds usually make the necro summon corpse robe the first robe made. We can summon a corpse every 25 secs for zero mana. This spell looked good on paper, but everyone is usually bound near a bank and can get a coffin from bank, summon their corpse, then use robe and coffins on corpse to summon everyone else.  To reduce the reuse time by 20% means I can use it every 58 min instead of 72. No real benefit there. Hastened Lifeburn would have been a much better choice.<br /><br />Hastened AE Undead Mez - Again :( useless spell is just made useless at a faster rate.<br /><br />Theft of Life - If this is for Necro, WTG :)<br />Fury of Magic - Woot, if useable by Necro… Job well done :)<br />Fury of Magic Mastery - See Above <claps><br /><br />7. An example of systemic apathy to our class… <br />Spell Line Progressions - When I was doing the spreadsheet, I started noticing that some classes were getting spells that we were not getting even though we started the line before they did. I also noticed that we had a lot of spell lines that just vanished. <br /><br />If the plan in PoP is to not adjust our support spells to make us more useful on raids. Then please adjust our damage spells to make us have some more impact on raids. It’s kind of ironic to be called the master of death and not really be able to flex any killing muscle.<br /><br />In particular, look at the spreadsheet lines  (176-216). Keep in mind Necro’s are supposed to be the Masters of Death, Fear, Disease, etc… and we are a PURE caster not a hybrid. Therefore our command of the arcane magics should be well above the bumbling Shaman class. <br /><br />Yet as you can see on the chart, even though we started the Single Target Disease Dots, and AE Disease Dots before Shaman. Starting at lvl 19, someone decided that Shaman should have a better control over disease than a  Necromancer. So even though we are more inclined to understand and control the energies of disease. (Which was also demonstrated thru our lvl ONE disease dot spell). After lvl 16 we only got 2 more disease Dots until the lame one in PoP. How is it that  a class that starts a line of spells ends up behind a class that got the spells after them and who isn’t even a pure casting class? What’s even more annoying, is the fact our lvl 65 spell (the zenith of a class spell) is a friggen disease spell that’s inferior to a disease spell already in game at lvl 59 for shaman (pox). If VI’s position is that shaman have a better control over disease than a necro, then why is our top spell a Disease spell instead of  Magic or Fire? Again, no thought given to the spells.<br /><br />We also started the Disease AE Dot spell (see spreadsheet Lines 126 thru 149 for AE spells) at lvl 16 and then never saw one again. What happened to that line of spells? Again, it seems no one took the time, or  effort to develop them for us it seems. But, they sure developed the shaman AE poison dots though.<br /><br />Wait! :) I’m not done. We also started the Poison DOT line of spells. See spreadsheet lines 193-207. Once again the shaman class got their second poison dot before we did. But then, when we both had same spell (VoS) it was assigned to us at 34 and shaman at 39. So, twice we had Poison dots before shaman and then at 49, shaman get EB and we have to wait till 51. Then they get one at 56 and another at 65. Then when we finally get one at  61, it is AGAIN inferior to a poison spell already in game at lvl 56 (Bane of Nife). <br /><br />Not done yet :). We also started Poison DD’s (see spreadsheet lines 210-216). We got first DD at 24, then again at 34. Shaman got their first one at 34. Then, we get ZERO new poison DD’s thru lvl 65. <br />Shaman get one at 44, and one at 61. <br /><br />I’m happy for the Shaman class, they have an excellent combination of new DD’s, Dots, Slows, Debuffs, Pets, Buffs, Heals, Cures, etc.. and can regen mana faster than even a necro can.  <br /><br />But, when I look at our class and see how we start a spell line, and then  have to play second fiddle to a class that isn’t even a pure caster, its frustrating. Especially, when the new PoP spells assigned to us, aren’t even as good as spells another class already has. And frankly, spells that should have been in our spell book too by now.<br /><br />It’s just further validation that no one is really looking at our class and taking care of it, they are just putting in a half assed effort and not even looking at  spells that are already in the natural progression in that line, and they make new ones for us that are worse than existing spells.<br /><br />8. Undead Mastery - As Masters of the Dead who are able to summon forth minions of  Death and extend control over their actions. It seems our control spells need a bit of tweaking. As a PURE caster class who is supposed to control undead mobs I think we should have the same type of undead AE stun, Single target mez and charm spells as the enchanters do for regular mobs. But what we have as a class is the ability to slow, mez for 18 secs tops, and charm some mobs for random amounts of time. The fact that we can’t lower MR on our undead targets, and the fact that we have generally very low charisma as a class means our charms don’t last anywhere near as long as enchanters. <br /><br />And in PoP our undead control spells are yet another example of no one looking at our class needs, and how we interact with others and just arbitrarily deciding to add a level to our mez spell and extending it to 30 secs and saying “well that’s a nice little upgrade for them”.<br /><br />I am a MASTER of DEATH Class! I can’t nuke well, I have decent dots, and a few utility spells, but in the expansion what do Necro get in added undead control? The ability to mez one level higher for 12 secs longer :(<br />And the lvl 65 charm, which I think is a great looking spell, but lets be real guys, less than 1% of the Necro community will ever see that spell I’m sure.<br /><br />The enchanter class got outstanding upgrades in mez, charm, stun, debuff lines. You did a wonderful job on them. But don’t you think that we should have some spells that charm higher level undead only somewhere between Thrall of Bones and Word of Terris? There is a lvl 60 fixed length undead charm spell, but a 30 sec charm and a five min recast makes it a useless spell basically. Useful maybe to break a certain spawn or as a emergency back up to chanters in the very few undead areas. <br /><br />Undead mastery for necro’s includes charm line, undead slow, undead fear, undead lull (which stopped at lvl 24). The fear and dots I can do to any mobs, so they aren’t really an upgrade to my mastery of the dead. So basically we have charm and slow as unique undead skills. No debuffs, no stuns,  no useable fixed length charms, no high level charms or mezz similar to what chanters have prior to PoP, not to mention the control they have on mobs after PoP. Are we the masters of the dead or not? If so, then why can’t we control the undead at least as well as a chanter could control them?<br /><br />It’s embarrassing to realize as a Master of Death, who has the supposedly omnipotent  ability to manipulate the minions of death , fear, and disease, that I can not nuke undead at least as well as a cleric. In fact the best undead DD I can do thru lvl 65 is 725 and now SK/Pally can undead nuke for 585 and 615. I can’t charm, mezz, or stun the undead anywhere near as well as a chanter. My summoned undead pets aren’t as strong as a Magi or a BST’s pet. And now we don’t even have the best dots anymore :( Funeral used to be the king of dots at 240 a tick for 9 ticks. My best dots I use (or try to use in fights) are 240, 205, 150, 123 a tick for a total of 40 ticks. In addition to their awesome debuffs, nukes, heals, buffs, man regen, etc.. Now Shaman can now dot for  320, 214, 130, 111 a tick for a total of 58 ticks. Hell even druids now have a 240 a tick dot for 6 ticks.  So, where am I a master of anything here? <br /><br />Ok enough of my whining :) I have suggestions I think will be helpful to our class. (Again, I’m speaking from a high end raid contribution standpoint. I’m looking for way to be able to contribute more to the success of the raid and my guild)<br /><br />1. Add a new Mana Tranfer spell similar in ratio to the summoned magi rod. Magi can summon a rod for 400 mana that gives someone 660 mana at a cost of  900 hps. The best I can do is send 150 mana to someone at a cost of 400 mana. So, my mana transfer spell is only 23% as effective as a magi rod. The loss of hps on ppl isn’t much of an impact at all. With bard heals, Regens, group/area heals, and other various heal spells no one really ever gets so low on heals that they can’t rod anymore.<br /><br />I’d like to see a transfer spell of 350-400 mana per 500 of my mana with same recast time etc as we have now.<br /><br />I’d also like to see a new Class AA similar to the Shaman Can5 spell. Where I could send  some one 75% of my mana to someone every three min or so.<br /><br />This one single change would do more for us being beneficial to raids than anything else you could do. And its not a new line of spells, its simply an extension of an existing line of spells.  You also can’t possibly use the argument that it will unbalance game play. Right now on raids we have 2-3 magi who do nothing but pump out tons of rods to lay on ground at cleric/caster  feet on raids. They alone can send mana way more efficiently than I can. But at least this skill will allow me to be close to what they can do and able to help when they aren’t able to make a raid.<br /><br />2. If you are not able or willing to adjust our dots to be more powerful than other classes. Then why don’t you make a Necro only skill that allows critical dots. Similar to the way wizards get critical DD’s starting at lvl 12. Then as a Arch AA skill you can add a critical dot fury available to all dot casters, and a Necro Only Class AA skill that has critical dot fury mastery just like wizards have for DD’s.<br /><br />You could add a dot caster Arch skill called Spell Casting Affliction Fury, and then replace our class Massive Group Buff skill with Spell Casting Affliction Fury Mastery restricted to Necro only.<br /><br />This can’t be a difficult thing to code. Simply double (or multiply by what ever variable you decide to use)  the damage done initially if there is initial damage and then adjust the damage each tick. It doesn’t need to extend the dot, just increase the damage per tick by some variable just like you do with the SCF AA skill 33%, 66% and 100%.<br /><br />I can’t see how you can make an argument against this either. Wizards already crank out massive damage on spells with their AA fury skills. Even if we were to double our damage output, it still takes the same time for the spell to run its course and we still wouldn’t be close to what damage a wizard can do.<br /><br />I would actually make the argument that we are now a damage dealing class because of the changes to our utility spells effectiveness, and in fact need these type of skills to allow us to be more effective damage dealers on raids.<br /><br /><br />3. Improve our DD spells - There is something wrong when at lvl 65 the best DD I could cast on a magic resistant mob is 510 :)<br /><br />Add a 900ish  fire/cold DD spell  in 58-60 range please. The spell added to our dd spells at lvl 55 was exactly the same spell we have at 44 except it doesn’t turn the mob into a skeleton.  A 510 DD with a 12 sec recast time really means we can’t use anything but life taps for DD’s.<br /><br />Speaking of life taps - These have the worse mana efficiency of any DD in game I think. But they are very useful to us because we are almost always in lich form. <br /><br />With that in mind, can you please revamp our lvl 60 life tap to be more useful. A spell that takes a essence emerald to cast and has a 15 min reuse time really shouldn’t even be in the game anymore.<br /><br />This spell if revamped would address our DD issue and  allow us to be more useful on raids when clearing dungeons to get to the boss mobs. Even if you left the mana to damage ratio the same as previous taps I think we could all live with that.<br /><br />Here’s what I was thinking. Make Trucidation a normal life tap spell by removing the recast time and essence emerald component. Increasing the mana for the spell to 600 mana which is in line with Touch of Night tap at 405 mana for 720 damage.<br /><br />That way you don’t have to make a new spell, you just use one we already have, just make it one people will actually use.<br /><br />Again I cant see how you can make an argument against this either. All other caster classes in PoP have a 1100 or higher damage spell. None of them have to pay 600 mana to cast it either. (see spreadsheet lines 49-86)<br />Also, we have been defined our whole EQ life by our ability to steal the very life essence from our targets, but we then don’t get any new taps since lvl 57? If you adjust trucidation to be useful then it would fall right in line with a typical lvl 60 spell. At 600 mana we won’t be casting it a lot, but at least we can have it to use when needed.<br /><br />Undead DD - Where is it? Cleric get a 1200 undead DD in PoP and we don’t. I find that a bit ridiculous. At lvl 65 the best undead DD I can use will be for 725. There has to be something in between. If you are making the argument clerics are better at undead DD’s (which I don’t disagree with entirely). Can you make a 925 undead DD or something? The fact SK/Pally can now do 585 when I can do only 725 as a pure caster at lvl 65 and the Master of Death is a bit embarrassing.<br /><br />4. Add some debuffs - Most of our group taps, some of our DD’s, are disease based. The one mob resist debuff we have is a poison based resist spell. The Scent line is also over written by the druid sunder line of spells. So, what happens is once we land scent which drops the mobs DR, it then is usually overwritten by something so we loose all DR debuffs. Shaman are the only class with a Disease only debuff spell. They have way to many things to do on raids to mem a DR debuff so that we can land some of our spells. So, many times we can’t really do much because the mobs resistance is to high to land a DR or PR spell.<br /><br />Can you add DR debuffs to our class? In particular, the Insidious Decay spell shaman get at 52 would be great, its irresistible, and then I can follow with scent to drop DR more. That way, later when a lot of the new SK tap spells which are disease based come online, I can be able to help debuff mobs and not have to have shaman add yet another debuff or spell to stuff they already have to do.<br /><br />Can you also look at some undead Malo type spells? It’s nice to have charm undead type spells, but even when I have a alt skill bonus item of 15% my charm on mobs really doesn’t last long at all. Sometimes it lasts 15 secs, and other times 2-3min tops. I use thrall of bones and it has a cap of like 20 min, but rarely will it ever last more than 3 min. With all the new resist rules, and our low charisma, a undead Malo type spell would be a great addition. I’m rather shocked we don’t have one already.  When I’m supposed to be the puppet master of the undead, I would think when it comes to undead control spells I would have nearly every control type spell chanters have, but have them restricted to the undead.<br /><br />5. Undead Control - Please review the level limits on our undead mezz and charm spells compared to the chanter line of spells. Feel free to add some new ones in between 57 and 65 too. :) I really think we should be able to control the undead as well as a chanter could control them, and have the control to charm as high a level undead mobs as they can. (actually, we should have a natural ability to do better undead control than a chanter could because we understand the dark magics better than they ever could, but that’s another issue for another day) <br /><br />6. Enhanced Fear spells - Why aren’t there any for Necro’s? There are tons of mezz spells for chanters over level 52, up to level 68 in fact. They can also charm up to level 64. I understand why they can charm and mezz that high. Because they can control the mind and that’s what they do. I can make an argument that Fear, in addition to Dots,  is what Necro’s do. But yet, I am unable to fear anything over lvl 52. Why isn’t there an upgraded fear spell available only to necros that can fear up to 60 or something?<br /><br />Also, because we have a understanding and control over the forces of Fear, why don’t we have a fearless AA skill?<br /><br />7. Massive Undead Dots - We have ONE undead dot, a level 29 spell that does 630 damage over 21 ticks for 140 mana. <br /><br />Perhaps you could add some undead dots between 29 and 65? Ones that get progressively more damaging and efficient. Perhaps one with same stats as the shaman dot blood of saryrn. As the top spell, and fill in level between 65 and 29 with stuff in between.<br /><br />8. Update some spell lines that just stopped. Such as:<br /><br />Banshee Aura<br /><br />Spirit Armor<br /><br />Shadow vortex<br /><br />Screaming Terror<br /><br />Corpral Empathy<br /><br />9. Death’s Silence PoP spell should be alteration skill not conjure.<br /><br /><br />Ok I have rambled on long enough. You probably hit delete key 3 pages ago J:) I really want to stay in this game. But please look at these concerns, and ask yourself “what exactly is a Necro’s role in EQ”. If we are masters of the undead, and  a dot class, then please update spells to reflect that.<br /><br />If you have any questions or want to vent on me for such a long letter :), please feel free to call or e-mail me.<br /><br /><br />Cuku<br /><br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=377117" target="_blank">http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=377117</a> <br /><br /><br /><br /> </span id="msg"></font>
           	</td>
                    </tr>
